You are working in a Flutter Melos workspace project. Follow the project rules strictly.

PROJECT TYPE:
- Flutter mobile app (Android/iOS)
- Melos multi-package workspace
- BLoC architecture
- Elixir navigation
- DependenciesScope based DI

FOLDER STRUCTURE (STRICT):
- Shared code → lib/src/common/
- Feature code → lib/src/feature/<feature_name>/
- Do NOT mix common and feature code
- Do NOT create new top-level folders without matching existing pattern
- Respect existing package/ structure (database, local_source, etc.)

DEPENDENCY INJECTION:
- App-wide dependencies are created ONLY in:
  lib/src/common/dependencies/initialization/
- Access dependencies via:
  context.dependencies
  DependenciesScope.of(context)
- Never manually recreate global dependencies inside features

STATE MANAGEMENT:
- Use flutter_bloc only
- Use Equatable states
- Use Bloc/Cubit pattern
- Use DroppableCubit or SequentialCubit when appropriate
- Feature/page scoped blocs must be created inside ElixirPage via BlocProvider(create:)
- Only use BlocProvider.value when instance comes from DI

BLOC NAVIGATION RULE (VERY IMPORTANT):
- NEVER pass BLoC instances between pages
- ONLY pass State between pages
- Next page must create a new BLoC using initialState parameter
- Follow this exact pattern:

  read state → pass state → create new bloc with initialState

NAVIGATION:
- Use Elixir pages only
- Define pages in lib/src/common/router/
- Navigate using context.push(...)
- Pages must extend AppPage / ElixirPage pattern already used

CONFIG:
- Runtime config comes from Config class
- Uses --dart-define and config/*.json
- Do not hardcode API URLs or environment values

CODE STYLE:
- Follow existing code style in project
- Max line length: 120
- Match naming and formatting from nearby files
- Keep widgets small and composable
- Do not create oversized classes

WHEN GENERATING CODE:
- First inspect similar feature files
- Copy existing architectural pattern
- Extend — do not redesign
- Do not introduce new state management or routing libraries
- Do not replace BLoC or Elixir

IF UNSURE:
- Follow the closest existing feature implementation
- Prefer consistency over creativity